# Explicit guardrail: internal handovers must stay local-only.
# Never put sensitive/operator handovers under docs/ or any tracked path.
# Match HANDOVER anywhere in the name (e.g. WINDOWS_AGENT_HANDOVER.md), not just a
# leading "HANDOVER_" — these files carry machine paths/usernames and must never ship.
*HANDOVER*.md
**/*HANDOVER*.md
HANDOVER_*.md
memory/HANDOVER_*.md
memory/INTERNAL_TAKEOVER*.md
memory/*TAKEOVER*.md
docs/HANDOVER_INTERNAL*.md
docs/INTERNAL_TAKEOVER*.md

# Personal / operator identity (never publish)
USER.md
IDENTITY.md
MEMORY.md
SOUL.md
AGENTS.md
HEARTBEAT.md
BOOTSTRAP.md
TOOLS.md
Cursor_Claude_Handover.md

# Handover docs (contain real node IPs, SSH paths, server configs)
docs/HANDOVER_2026-03-15_FULL_STATE.md
docs/HANDOVER_2026-03-14_HIVE_SURFACES_AND_RUNTIME_TRUTH.md

# Ops scripts (contain deployment IPs, SSH paths, server configs)
ops/*
!ops/llm_eval.py
!ops/ensure_public_hive_auth.py
!ops/pytest_shards.py
!ops/greenloop_concurrency.py
# Config-driven cluster launchers — pure glue (take --config <path>), no IPs/secrets.
# Without these negations the ops/* rule silently swallows them, so the bootstrap +
# cluster READMEs reference scripts that can never be committed.
!ops/run_meet_node_from_config.py
!ops/run_brain_hive_watch_from_config.py
tests/test_overnight_reports.py
tests/test_repo_hygiene_check.py
tests/test_channel_gateway.py

# Cluster configs (contain node IPs and auth tokens)
config/meet_clusters/do_ip_first_4node/
!config/meet_clusters/do_ip_first_4node/
!config/meet_clusters/do_ip_first_4node/**
config/meet_clusters/separated_watch_4node/tls/

# Internal deployment handover docs (contain server IPs, SSH commands)
docs/HANDOVER_PUBLIC_HIVE_*.md

